&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Mammoth Brands&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mammoth Brands (formerly Harry’s Inc.) is the modern CPG company behind brands Harry’s, Flamingo, Lume, Mando, and Coterie. We’re building a new model—and home—brands, founders, and talent looking to solve unmet needs, improve peoples’ lives, and ultimately challenge the status quo. Our mission is to “Create Things People Like More.” Simply put: everything we do should be better than what already exists. If it’s not, we don’t do it. This guides everything we do, from developing the best product experiences, to making Mammoth Brands a great place to work, to exploring innovative ways to give back to our community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We got our start in 2013 when our co-founders created Harry&#39;s. They built the brand differently—online first, prioritizing direct relationships with customers—and in the process learned they’d created something bigger: a playbook and platform that could help other brands grow and scale to their full potential, and a vision to reimagine consumer packaged goods. Today, Mammoth Brands is a growing portfolio of brands and the largest CPG company built in the last 20 years. Even as we grow, we take extra care to maintain the small, scrappy, entrepreneurial culture that helped to get us where we are today: to create a company that people like more, that better serves its customers, employees, and community. As a company, we’re also committed to making a positive impact and have donated over $20 million through our network of nonprofit partners to date.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Advanced Manufacturing Engineer assumes a high level of responsibility supporting the implementation of new manufacturing technologies across various sites. This engineer will collaborate cross-functionally with R&amp;amp;D/Product Development, Supply Chain, and Quality Engineering to develop manufacturing processes and custom equipment that will bring Harry’s next generation products into mass production. Additionally, this role will support existing manufacturing by developing specifications for new equipment to help scale the business globally. Successful candidates can learn fast and work independently. They can work in a cross-functional environment with a global presence developing new manufacturing processes and machinery in line with the needs of the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will accomplish&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Initiating, leading, and executing on product industrialization activities including equipment selection, process development, process characterization and process validation, in support of existing product changes and new product development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performing design for manufacturing/automation, equipment, and labor capacity planning. Driving key performance indicators such as Technical Capability, Cost,Timing, Performance, Quality, Yield and Availability throughout projects and into production.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Providing in-depth knowledge of problem solving linked to manufacturing processes and equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with cross-functional team members throughout product development phases to ensure program success. Supporting internal and external manufacturing, and site to site manufacturing transfer projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Making data driven decisions using appropriate analytical methodologies. Employing equipment, processes and procedures which promote a healthy, safe, and secure work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Driving industrialization efforts by collaborating cross-functionally on key software and controls projects.&lt;/li&gt;
